ctions show it as such.... too bad FD worked then probably he would of been gone. <br><br>Unfortunately assholes like this find a home  like SolB and try to stay there forever... <br>I wonder why he didn't take Noble? Seems very few people camp him. Or the loose ones near the entrance?<br>I hope things worked out after awhile...<br> <p>Tell Lespartan<br>Warrior<br>Member of Forgotten Horde<br><BR><DIV ALIGN="CENTER"><A HREF="http://clubs.lycos.com/live/events/september11.asp"><IMG SRC="http://a1032.g.akamai.net/f/1032/81/30m/www.gamesville.lycos.com/art_gv/ribbon_small.gif" ALT="[Flag Campaign icon]" WIDTH="49" HEIGHT="86" BORDER="0" ALIGN="MIDDLE"><BR>Support freedom</A></DIV><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ualundraadjani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AlundraAdjani</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.theroyalknights.org/sigs/btnappheartred.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Whore</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/20/01 3:34:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshitlistpeopletowatchoutforonourserver.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=703.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.theroyalknights.org/sigs/appquistis.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: KSing and dishonorable monk Kanos</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  He asked me to take one, but I didn't want to take one cause he can call me a KSer since I took his agro<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Actually, the definition of KSing states that you must kill something already aggrod *without consent* of the aggrod player.  So, if he really did say this, he gave you &quot;consent&quot; to kill it and you were not KSing.  Just like killing the skeleton on the noob who is /yelling is not KSing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usijandistraightarrow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sijandistraightarrow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/20/01 9:10:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumshitlistpeopletowatchoutforonourserver.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=703.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: KSing and dishonorable monk Kanos</span><hr size=1> True Alundra, but would you trust someone like this to admit they asked for help after the fact ? I wouldn't lift a finger to help him in any way after the attitude and behaviour exhibited. That is one good  thing about being in that position. There is no obligation to assist another players under any circumstances. If someone doesn't want to be courteous, considerate and cooperative that player can hardly expect anyone to assist. It's not one of my better personality traits, but I have stood and laughed at players such as they die. Normally I'm more than willing to help other players, asking only recognition as another person - not being treated like an npc, such as saying hello before asking for ANYTHING - or approaching in a roleplay manner. For players who thinks it's perfectly acceptable to walk up and say something such as &quot;SOW PlZ ThX&quot; I have no inclination to assist in any manner. It doesn't take much effort to show a little courtesy. Saying hello to another person before asking for anything, no matter how small, is the least a person should expect. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title