into the room he was attacking one Kobold, and another one had just spawned and turned his way and threw a punch, At this time I really honestly didnt know that he knew if he was fighting 2 of them, and simply hit the one he was not attacking. Now it may have been bad on my part and some can argue that it wasn't. Sometimes we ask people if they need help, sometimes we assume they do, sometimes we think they wont mind if one is taken, sometimes they will.  It's not a special camp, there was probably several kobolds spawned besides this one, yeah thats true, but tell me how big of a deal it really is in SOLB (Train City) and mass confusion, to attack one of the 2 kobolds in a room of the camp you are sharing? Worth calling a GM? Worth posting a 5 page essay on the lanys boards? Or worth replying to the 5 page essay? Nahh, I think not. The thing that should piss you off on a Kill steal is the blatent running up to your little called area, hacking away at the mob you are currently fighting, taking the EXP and loot. Lets try not to blow things like this in places like that out of proportion peoples. I was in the wrong, He was in the wrong, yet none of it was serious. As for the GM, it always depends on the situation and GM as to who's fault it was, and who should do what, but all it boils down to is that one of the people either leaves, they share, the person logs, you make a friend, you make an enemy. Now you can all jump on the bandwagon and be against this disastrous and unbelieveable deed that I have done if you wanna, but take a look at the overall outcome and meaning. Take a look at the world around you latley and come and tell me if this type of shit is the important stuff. <br><br>Kanos/Stryyfe/Karnavor/....if you wanna know my other characters, give me a tell. Cya <p><a href="http://www.angelfire.com/realm2/jesse_1/images/Vengeance.jpg/"<img src="http://www.angelfire.com/realm2/jesse_1/images/Vengeance.jpg" border="0"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcol